From d98be56b8ce759fd0afb110302a80fff437f87e2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Patrick Gill <patrickgill@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 23:48:03 +1000
Subject: [PATCH 08/13] Fix stack-passed call arguments across blocks and large
 frames; add --annotate=source

Three related fixes/features, all found and verified against real
tenchu-decomp functions (KPRINTF_OBJ_140, AdtMessageBox):

- Cross-block subroutine_args resolution: create_dominated_node_state now
  inherits not-yet-consumed stack-passed call arguments from the immediate
  dominator (via the existing locs_clobbered_until_dominator machinery,
  extended to StackLocations), so an outgoing-argument store GCC hoisted
  into an earlier block (e.g. a branch's delay slot) still resolves at a
  call site reached after a merge, instead of "Unable to find stack arg".
  Genuinely ambiguous cases (a fork with different definitions) still fall
  through to the original error, unchanged.

- Large-frame prologue support: get_stack_info now recognizes GCC's
  large-frame idiom (subu $sp,$sp,$temp then addu $alias,$temp,$sp to
  recompute the pre-adjustment $sp for callee-save stores that need a
  small, encodable offset) via a new sp_alias_regs tracker, fixing two
  independent bugs it caused: is_leaf staying wrongly True (breaking
  in_subroutine_arg_region for the whole function), and evaluate.py's
  deref() misreading "$alias = $sp + allocated_stack_size" as "address of
  the first incoming stack argument", corrupting negative-offset stores
  through it into phantom arg0.unkN field writes.

- --annotate=source: prefixes each statement with a `// FILE:LINE:
  mnemonic args` comment naming its source instruction. Built as an
  extensible kind-set (Options.annotate/GlobalInfo.annotate: FrozenSet[str],
  ANNOTATION_KINDS as the single validated list) so future annotation kinds
  don't need new CLI/Options/GlobalInfo threading -- just a new string and
  a producer function in source_annotate.py.

Tests: 380 passed, 0 skipped, 1 failed (pre-existing, unrelated
e2e:weird-asm/test.s), 381 total. New fixtures: stack-arg-cross-block-
resolved, stack-arg-cross-block-ambiguous, stack-arg-large-frame-alias-base.
Full narrative writeup: /Users/pjg/devel/projects/ps1/decomp/tenchu/docs/m2c.md
